## R Task

Please follow the directions listed below

1.  Download the task files

<center>
<a onclick="fetch(&#39;data:application/zip;base64,&#39;).then(res =&gt; res.blob()).then(blob =&gt; {&#10;      const downloadURL = window.URL.createObjectURL(blob);&#10;      const a = document.createElement(&#39;a&#39;);&#10;      document.body.appendChild(a);&#10;      a.href = downloadURL;&#10;      a.download = &#39;Simple Regression Task.zip&#39;; a.click();&#10;      window.URL.revokeObjectURL(downloadURL);&#10;      document.body.removeChild(a);&#10;    });">
<button class="btn btn-primary hvr-sweep-to-left"><i class="fa fa-save"></i> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style='color:#ffffff'>Download</span></button>
</a>
</center>

<br>

2.  [Unzip](/resources/unzipping) them on your computer and place all of the files in a folder of your choice as is

3.  Open the file `Simple Regression Install.R` and run the syntax to install the **pacman** package. This can be used not just to load libraries, but if you are missing any then those will be downloaded automatically by R

4.  Open the file `Simple Regression walkthrough.Rmd` in RStudio

5.  After finishing the walkthrough, open the mostly empty Rmarkdown file `Simple Regression Report.Rmd`, read through the directions, and include your syntax to receive credit. You are provided an optional `Simple Regression test script.R` to test your R code as needed.

6.  Save the resulting PDF file by adding your first initial and last name to the beginning of the filename. For example, my submission would be `aroy Simple Regression walkthrough.pdf`

7.  Submit the script to [eCampus](https://ecampus.wvu.edu) in the Submission Portal
